opening_comment: There's a software bug that prevents OpenStreetMap from calculating directions between Matei, Fiji and Wairiki, Fiji.  Namely, the crux of the problem is that the route would cross the 180-degree meridian.  OpenStreepMap sees this as a mathematical singularity, and becomes quite helpless.  Believe it or not, this problem also affects two roads in Siberia.  It really bugs me...  please fix it, OpenStreetMap developers!
